The paper discusses the challenges and opportunities in automating robot design, which is a topic that falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the role of models in robot design, which is a topic that falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the design of the internal state of the robot and how task specifications are designed within this context, which are topics that fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also considers the human-element within the envisioned scheme, which is a topic that falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
